gomodel:SYNGO_1117  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Kainate receptor GluR5 (=GRIK1).\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has ligand-gated ion channel receptor activity and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (shown with high-resolution technique). The inference to term ligand-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099507) is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P22756] SyNGO ID 1114 (PMID:16360275, EM). Experimental description: Isolation and expression of GluR-5 clones\nForPCR (MullisandFalooona, 1987),oligonucleotideprimersandreaction conditionswereasdescribed(Keinanenetal.,1990).RatforebraincDNA was used as a template. The PCR product (- 500 bp) was gel-purified, cleaved with EcoRI and KpnI, subcloned into doubly cut M13mpl9 RF- DNA (Yanisch-Perronetal.,1985)andsequenced(Sangeretal.,1977). A PCR-generatedDNA fragmentofaGluR-5specificM 13subclonewas internalylabelledwith[3P]dCTPtoaspecificactivityof2x 109/Igand usedasaprobetoscreenaratforebraincDNA libraryconstructedinX- Zap (Stratagene). Five independent cDNAs from these screens were subclonedintopBluescriptSK plasmidvectors(Stratagene,CA) orM13mpl8 andmpl9RF-DNA (Yanisch-Perronetal.,1985)andthesesubcloneswere used for sequence analysis (Sanger et al., 1977). Expression constructs of GluR-5-2 specifying different C-termini were engineered by subcloning 3' BamnHI-AoI or BamHI-EcoRI fragments encoding C-termini of GluR-5-2aor-2-c,respectively,anda5'HindLH-BamHI fragmentdirectly intoamammalianexpressionvectorwithaCMV promoter(Gormanetal.,\n1990).TheheterogeneityconcerningglutamineandargininecodonsinTM2 wasgeneratedbyexchanginga400bpBspEI-MscIfragmentcoveringTM regionsItoImofeditedandnon-editedGIuR-5cDNA clones. Theconstructs wereusedtotransfecthumanembryonickidneycels293(ATCC CRL 1573)asdescribed(ChenandOkayama, 1987;Pritcheletal.,1989).These were subjected to binding studies and electrophysiology." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_1117" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

